How many positive 4-digit integers have only odd digits?
inference:
The digits that can be used are 1, 3, 5, 7, 9.
For a 4-digit integer, the first digit can be any of the 5 odd digits.
The second digit can be any of the 5 odd digits.
The third digit can be any of the 5 odd digits.
The fourth digit can be any of the 5 odd digits.
The number of such 4-digit integers is $5 \times 5 \times 5 \times 5 = 5^4 = 625$.
Final Answer: $\boxed{625}$
ground_truth: Each of the 4 digits can be one of the 5 odd digits: 1, 3, 5, 7, 9. So there are $5\times 5\times 5\times 5=\boxed{625}$ such 4-digit numbers.
